3.4.1.2 Functions: poll_sensors(), normalize_data() 
3.4.2 AI Brain 
3.4.2.1 Attributes: model_weights_path, current_policy 
3.4.2.2 Functions: evaluate_state(), calculate_reward(). 



3.5  Non-Functional Requirements
State the requirements in measurable terms 
3.5.1 Performance: The complete monitoring and execution loop shall be processed in less than 50ms. CPU overhead must not exceed 1.5%. 
3.5.2 Reliability: The system requires a "Dead Man's Switch" daemon to instantly restore Windows default settings if the main process crashes. 
3.5.3 Security: Telemetry data must be securely stored locally in encrypted files. Zero external network transmission is permitted. 
3.5.4 Portability: The Hardware Abstraction Layer must allow the software to function across varying AMD and Intel processor architectures without code modification
3.7  Logical Database Requirements 
The system utilizes a local SQLite3 database. It requires two tables: telemetry_logs (tracking historical hardware states) and game_profiles (tracking user-defined target thresholds for specific executables). 
3.8  Design Constraints 
3.8.1 Standards Compliance 
All Python code must strictly comply with PEP-8 formatting standards and modular Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) paradigms. 












